  "prompt": "Is Trump's victory good for Indians who are planning to study in USA in 2017?",
  "response": "The impact of Trump's presidency on international students, including those from India, was mixed during his term. Some key points:\n\n1. Challenges:\n- Stricter visa policies and immigration restrictions\n- More scrutiny on student and work visas\n- Potential travel ban concerns\n- Reduced H1B visa approvals\n\n2. Potential Positives:\n- Some universities maintained welcoming policies\n- STEM students had certain advantages\n- No complete ban on international students\n\n3. Recommendations for Indian students:\n- Carefully research university policies\n- Prepare strong visa applications\n- Consider alternate documentation\n- Stay informed about changing immigration rules\n\n4. Specific considerations in 2017:\n- Increased uncertainty in immigration landscape\n- Some students felt psychological impact of potential restrictions\n- Strong academic credentials became more important\n\nOverall, while the environment was challenging, many Indian students still successfully pursued studies in the USA during this period. Individual experiences varied based on specific circumstances.\n\nNote: Immigration policies can change, so it's always recommended to consult current official sources and university international student offices for the most up-to-date information.",
